        <headline>Flood Advisory issued August 3 at 5:56AM EDT until August 3 at 6:45AM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast South Carolina, including the
following county, Beaufort.

* WHEN...Until 645 AM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 556 AM EDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin
shortly in the advisory area. Between 3 and 5 inches of rain
have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts of 0.5 to 1 inch are expected
over the area. This additional rain will result in minor
flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Hilton Head Island, Forest Beach, Folly Field, Hilton Head
Airport, Lawton, Calibogue Cay, Sea Pines, Harbortown, Wilton
Graves Bridge and Shelter Cove.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
